item.title: CVE-2020-24561|2024-08-04T15:19:07.396Z -- trend%20micro -- trend%20micro%20serverprotect%20for%20linux
item.description: A command injection vulnerability in Trend Micro ServerProtect for Linux 3.0 could allow an attacker to execute arbitrary code on an affected system. An attacker must first obtain admin/root privileges on the SPLX console to exploit this vulnerability.
